result: Answer 154) In January 2013, 1 794 272 admissions and 1 765 372 dismissals were declared in Brazil, ie 28 900 job vacancies were created, according to data from the General Register of Employees and Unemployed (Caged), released by the Ministry of Work and Employment (MTE). According to Caged, the number of vacancies created in January 2013 suffered a 75%drop, when compared to the same period of 2012.
